      {
        "paragraph_index": 1,
        "text": "### Why?\n\nNIST SRD-46 (the *Critically Selected Stability Constants of Metal Complexes* database) is focused exclusively on **aqueous-phase** equilibrium data. Supercritical CO₂ (scCO₂) is used in some specialized extraction and coordination chemistry studies, but those data are not compiled in this particular reference database. For metal-complex equilibria in scCO₂, you would need to consult primary literature sources (e.g., studies on uranyl–TBP or lanthanide–β-diketonate complexes in scCO₂).\n\n*Source: NIST Standard Reference Database 46*",
